// Headless probe for the HDR calibration example. Which path it exercises
// depends on the runner's backend: macOS Metal negotiates an scRGB-linear
// surface unconditionally (EDR), so CI hits the real scRGB encode path there;
// on backends that report no HDR surface the scRGB-linear request resolves
// back to plain SDR (warn + degrade) and the patterns render through the
// byte-identical SDR pipeline. Either way the example runs to a screenshot.
// Frame 200 leaves headroom for surface (re)negotiation and the first pattern
// to settle.
(
    setup: (
        fixed_frame_time: Some(0.05),
    ),
    events: [
        (200, ScreenshotAndExit),
    ]
)
